As of the 2010 census Solomon had a population of 426.  The ethnic and racial composition of the population was 75.8% Hispanic, 20.9% non-Hispanic white, 0.2% Native American, 0.7% Asian Indian, 0.7% other Asian and 2.8% reporting two or more races.<ref>2010 demographic date for Solomon, Arizona from the US census</ref>
